headline: Insider Trading Fears Surface As Super Bowl Ad Prediction Market Grows
summary: In the lead up to Super Bowl 60, prediction market platforms have started offering contracts on which companies will run ads during the game. This new development has sparked concerns about the potential for insider trading. Prediction market platforms, Kalshi and Polymarket, have initiated contracts on which companies will advertise during Super Bowl 60, set to take place on Feb. 8 in Santa Clara, California. headline: Coca-Cola’s Argentina Investment And AI Push Shape Growth And Valuation
summary: Coca Cola (NYSE:KO) plans to invest $1.4b in Argentina. The investment is aimed at expanding growth and manufacturing capacity in the country. The company is also focusing on international expansion, portfolio diversification, and use of digital technology and AI in its operations. Coca Cola, the global beverages group behind its flagship soda brand and a wide range of non alcoholic drinks, is leaning further into international markets with this new commitment to Argentina.
